1
00:00:03,420 --> 00:00:07,080
oṁ ajñāna-timirāndhasya jñānāñjana-śalākayā

2
00:00:07,680 --> 00:00:11,640
cakṣur unmīlitaṁ yena tasmai śrī-gurave namaḥ

3
00:00:12,880 --> 00:00:14,520
It's all about seeing

4
00:00:17,060 --> 00:00:19,460
and, in a sense, observation

5
00:00:22,700 --> 00:00:32,200
Guru Maharaj said rishi... it's interesting word - the Sanskrit word for creation is shristi

6
00:00:32,980 --> 00:00:36,660
has r/s in there, but s in the beginning. Sristi - like

7
00:00:36,660 --> 00:00:45,260
srishti sthiti-pralaya-sadhana-saktir eka/ chayeva yasya bhuvanani bibharti durga

8
00:00:45,260 --> 00:00:51,080
In "Brahma-samhita", talking about creation - but Guru Maharaj said

9
00:00:51,080 --> 00:00:59,800
one of the meanings of word rishi... That's in "Gita": tad viddhi praṇipātena/ paripraśnena sevayā

10
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:06,460
upadekṣyanti te jñānaṁ/ jñāninas tattva-darśinaḥ

11
00:01:06,460 --> 00:01:10,800
The tattva-darshi, darshis

12
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:17,100
darshan -  we think, O, darshan - that's when you go to see the Guru or the Vaishnava

13
00:01:17,100 --> 00:01:22,860
and that's correct, but you'll see the
word use like "sat darshan"

14
00:01:22,860 --> 00:01:26,820
in six different types of philosophies - but what does that mean - "sat darshan"?

15
00:01:26,820 --> 00:01:32,780
darshan is "philosophy", means: perspective, ways of seeing

16
00:01:32,780 --> 00:01:36,780
so Guru Maharaj said the rishis

17
00:01:36,780 --> 00:01:41,700
they are seeing and experiencing the
Truth. And by the truth - remember

18
00:01:41,700 --> 00:01:48,620
we always mean Krishna, a person - not the
truth in some abstract form

19
00:01:48,620 --> 00:01:59,520
The Truth is Krishna. Krishna is the Truth. īśvaraḥ paramaḥ kṛṣṇaḥ/ sac-cid-ānanda-vigrahaḥ

20
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:05,000
There is no non-vigraha truth - really

21
00:02:05,020 --> 00:02:17,380
so seeing some perspective
shanta dasya sakhya vatsalya madhura

22
00:02:17,380 --> 00:02:25,960
svakiya parakiya - different ways, devotional a way of seeing

23
00:02:30,580 --> 00:02:38,140
so that's - as a poet said - the deep heart's core and then it's coming out

24
00:02:38,140 --> 00:02:47,360
in the form of the mantra, the scripture, the song, the hari-katha

25
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:59,760
so they're not authors in the conventional sense - or creators - like, you know, in the creative sense

26
00:02:59,760 --> 00:03:05,900
even the leading American literary critic
Harold Bloom, he wrote a book called

27
00:03:05,900 --> 00:03:10,640
one is "The Anatomy of Influence", the other one's "The Anxiety of Influence"

28
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:17,780
so what he's saying is these modern writers often, if not all the time

29
00:03:17,780 --> 00:03:21,200
they try to present themselves as though
they're like mushrooms

30
00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:27,440
they just sprung out of the soil of the muse, they're not under anyone's influence

31
00:03:27,440 --> 00:03:34,420
they're just giving something original
and that's why they're so great and wonderful

32
00:03:34,420 --> 00:03:46,240
but he says, To be inspired is
to be influenced and that's more... that we can support

33
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:54,940
tene brahma hṛdā in the Bhagavatam: the inspiration of Brahma is on account of divine influence

34
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:59,820
he's under divine influence and therefore there's inspiration

35
00:03:59,820 --> 00:04:02,300
so all devotees will think like that

36
00:04:02,300 --> 00:04:06,600
whenever someone is offering praise toward what they've expressed

37
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:11,880
they defer that praise to under whose influence they are

38
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:15,740
Guru...Saddhu, shastra, Guru, Vaishnav

39
00:04:15,740 --> 00:04:25,600
which is... they're not just being humble - which they are, but they're telling the truth

40
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:29,480
and then people will mistakenly think

41
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:34,960
Oh, then, you know,  we don't get to offer
anything new -  it's always just repeating

42
00:04:34,960 --> 00:04:40,060
something from the past or rote
recitation - no

43
00:04:40,060 --> 00:04:45,860
like Rupa Goswami's: rasoddama kamarbuda-madhura-dhamojjvala-tanur

44
00:04:45,860 --> 00:04:48,460
about Mahaprabhu and Chaitanya-astakam

45
00:04:48,460 --> 00:04:52,220
then Guru Maharaj under the influence of Rupa Goswami

46
00:04:52,220 --> 00:04:57,120
koṭi-kāma-mūrchchhitāṅghri-rūpa-rāsa-raṅgaraṁ

47
00:04:57,160 --> 00:04:59,080
similar - same same, but different

48
00:04:59,080 --> 00:05:04,700
so under his influence something has
sprung out

49
00:05:06,220 --> 00:05:14,940
and, you can say - and I'm just saying this in a happy way that will please...

50
00:05:14,940 --> 00:05:24,080
the Guru is pleased that the disciple like the parents are pleased if the child exceeds them

51
00:05:24,080 --> 00:05:32,840
so, you can say, in a sense, like - what Guru Maharaj - he took that and made it even more

52
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:38,860
and maybe Rupa Goswami is pleased with that: under his influence something even

53
00:05:38,860 --> 00:05:43,159
as wonderful or more wonderful was
expressed

54
00:05:43,160 --> 00:05:49,400
he says: rasoddama kamarbuda-madhura-dhamojjvala-tanur

55
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:57,720
discussing the beauty and sweetness of Mahaprabhu that  rasoddama, rasa udama kamar, you know

56
00:05:57,720 --> 00:06:05,280
billions of Cupids in full-blown
cupidity - and I'm re-purposing that word

57
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:14,360
that points toward the sweetness: madhura-dhamojjvala-tanur - of Mahaprabhu

58
00:06:14,360 --> 00:06:20,240
so he's doing like that and
it's similar to Brahma-samhita

59
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:24,920
kandarpa-koti-kamaniya-visesa-sobham

60
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:27,920
but Guru Maharaj says in his verse

61
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:33,100
koṭi-kāma-mūrchchhitāṅghri-rūpa-rāsa-raṅgaraṁ

62
00:06:33,100 --> 00:06:38,320
that 10 million Cupid's will faint to see the
beauty of Mahaprabhu

63
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:42,560
so he's taken this and expressed it in a
new way

64
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:48,360
but it's under the influence of Srila Rupa Goswami

65
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:54,760
so really to be inspired is to be influenced and that is a good thing

66
00:06:54,760 --> 00:07:04,140
but those who lack humility cannot accept that

67
00:07:04,140 --> 00:07:13,280
humility defined as the perceived proximity of greatness

68
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:19,560
of that which is greater than yourself

69
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:24,820
that floods the heart with genuine feelings
of humility

70
00:07:24,820 --> 00:07:31,300
the perception of the proximity of greatness - that which is greater than you

71
00:07:31,300 --> 00:07:37,720
and so can say: divinity the greater Vaishnavas, the scriptures - so many things

72
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:42,260
but there are cinmoy threads connecting all these things

73
00:07:42,280 --> 00:07:55,900
so the rishis seeing, experiencing, expressing the truth under the influence of divine current

74
00:07:55,900 --> 00:08:03,320
so, you know, they said that [there are] cinmoy threads that are connecting these things

75
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:11,480
so we know yesterday there was mention of the Chinese New Year and I like to say

76
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:17,100
the Year of the Boar. I'm comfortable
saying that

