00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:58,720
withdraw His beautiful limbs within His
form and show a hard shell

98
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:05,340
so she's going through Das avatars in another way:  gopi-vision

99
00:11:05,340 --> 00:11:17,840
They can do that. But meanwhile - back on Earth and more specifically - Varaha

100
00:11:19,380 --> 00:11:26,400
we're told in various pastimes that Varahadev rescues the Earth

101
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:34,400
Simple enough expression. But how does
that... That should connect -  if we say there are

102
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:41,780
chinmoy threads connecting everything and why Krishna and...

103
00:11:41,780 --> 00:11:51,100
So in Bhagavad-gita He says, yadā yadā hi dharmasya/ glānir bhavati bhārata

104
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:59,240
abhyutthānam adharmasya/ tadātmānaṁ sṛjāmy aham - whenever... We know what it says

105
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:05,380
I'm just gonna say it in a different way, you know: at the point where religion becomes irreligion

106
00:12:05,380 --> 00:12:14,040
at that time He needs to come down or send some avatar, representative,  etc.

107
00:12:14,040 --> 00:12:20,920
because as we told, prakṛti-vaicitryād - pāramparyeṇa... prakṛti-vaicitryād

108
00:12:20,920 --> 00:12:26,680
The truth given - Bhaktivinod Thakur says in the Bhagavatam - in its purity in the beginning

109
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:29,440
but then it's modified - Uddhava, 11th Canto

110
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:33,540
modified by the temperament of the
receivers

111
00:12:33,540 --> 00:12:40,320
and then it gradually starts moving away from that

112
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:52,460
like the classic exercise in journalism class
where, say, there's

113
00:12:52,470 --> 00:12:58,500
four rows, ten students in each row and
the teacher will go and tell the student

114
00:12:58,500 --> 00:13:04,040
in the first row, whisper something to
them - and then they have to turn around

115
00:13:04,040 --> 00:13:07,240
and tell the next student, next-next, go up and down the row like this

116
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:12,540
and then they get to the end, and then
what she says: before the class

117
00:13:12,540 --> 00:13:17,840
they have the last students here and - what? what were you told? - and they tell what they were told

118
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:20,880
and then they ask the first student what they were told

119
00:13:20,880 --> 00:13:27,300
and then everybody breaks out in laughter
it's just turned into something else and

120
00:13:27,300 --> 00:13:35,540
the telling modified by the
temperament of the receiver minimally

121
00:13:35,540 --> 00:13:46,880
what to speak of other things
so He says, I will appear at those times and also

122
00:13:46,880 --> 00:13:56,760
paritranaya sadhunam/ vinasaya ca duskrtam/
dharma-samsthapanarthaya/ sambhavami yuge yuge

123
00:13:56,760 --> 00:14:00,820
repeatedly, yuga after yuga, almost like a hint

124
00:14:00,820 --> 00:14:09,300
of yuga avatars: yuge yuge
but yuga-avatars, lila-avatars,

125
00:14:09,300 --> 00:14:16,520
purusha-avatars, guna-avatars, you know,
shaktyavesha-avatars

126
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:28,500
manvantars - there's like a half a million manvantars,
you know, in a certain time period

127
00:14:34,140 --> 00:14:43,400
so He says in Gita - what we take to be
general principles are laid down there

128
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:49,900
but our Acharyas - they can extract from
there something more specific or

129
00:14:49,900 --> 00:14:55,200
a deeper level reading - like Guru Maharaja's
"Hidden Treasure of the Sweet Absolute"

130
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:59,380
showing in a nutshell shlokas and, you
know, yena mam upayantite

131
00:14:59,380 --> 00:15:08,760
parakiya-bhav, etc. - he can extract that,
but just taking it as it is

132
00:15:08,760 --> 00:15:19,980
it's laid the groundwork for so many avatars - so it's there - by inference or allusion

133
00:15:19,980 --> 00:15:28,840
and why did Krishna descend on the Earth? - 
we're told: to relieve the burden

134
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:37,040
so many demonic kings were populating the Earth
it was burdening the Earth

135
00:15:37,040 --> 00:15:44,480
and what is a visual to accompany that? - 
like the form of a hunchback woman

136
00:15:44,480 --> 00:15:52,700
due to so much weight, unbearable weight of these evil persons

137
00:15:52,700 --> 00:15:59,940
she's bent over and hunchbacked
like that

138
00:16:05,080 --> 00:16:09,000
but we have the Bhagavatam saying,
the Earth was plunged into

139
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:19,280
the nether regions - like the Garbhadak ocean
the Southern - like the Patagonia

140
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:32,280
of the Universe and Varahadev enters
the waters and how interesting - what is

141
00:16:32,280 --> 00:16:41,880
the speciality of the boar?
What is that European delicacy?

142
00:16:41,880 --> 00:16:50,000
Truffles! - So they use them
because they have this heightened sense

143
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:56,300
of smell to find them - otherwise they
can't find them, so this is the delight

144
00:16:56,300 --> 00:17:01,730
one of the delightful aspects of
Krishna's pastimes - He's omniscient

145
00:17:01,730 --> 00:17:11,980
