00:17:45,360 --> 00:17:50,620
the seventh chapter: puṇyo gandhaḥ
gandhaḥ means fragrance

153
00:17:50,620 --> 00:17:59,180
puṇyo gandhaḥa pṛthi - pṛthi means the earth
I am the fragrance of the earth

154
00:17:59,180 --> 00:18:07,780
all fragrances come out from the earth, the
soil, right? the lilavadee, goloka champak, plumeria

155
00:18:07,780 --> 00:18:11,990
that flower - it starts, it comes
out of the earth, but so does the

156
00:18:11,990 --> 00:18:19,240
fragrance of the Lotus and all other
flowers - so how wonderful is the earth

157
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:26,480
and it produced all these fruits, flowers,
etc. - from one soil all of these things

158
00:18:26,480 --> 00:18:34,640
come and He sings in the Gita: think of
that as Me - don't be afraid of it or

159
00:18:34,640 --> 00:18:42,860
or think that by thinking about it you're
necessarily lost in some sort of

160
